caption: I absolutely love this spot.  The food and drinks were delicious and the prices were great, especially for Waikiki.
Huge menu and they're open later than other bars. My wife says the spicy udon is amazing.  We came here after other bars had closed at 2200.  Busy, but not packed.
So glad we found this place! So glad we could get a table on the patio! We shared several dishes, each one beautifully prepared and righteously delicious. Would love to visit again on future trip.
Delicious.

Good food, good mixed drinks and nice atmosphere but my 3 of my friends finished their meals and my 4th friend literally had 1 scoop left before I finally got my dinner. I also asked for a glass of water which I never received.

When I sat down, I finished ordering immediately, but I waited 30 minutes, so I urged the waiter and passed another 10 minutes. A young boy attendant told me that he forgot to place the order. It's ridiculous. I wasted 40 minutes. I even didn’t get a cup of water.

We stumbled upon this place today while looking for a place for dinner.  Saw the rooftop, and the vibes were perfect so decided to go up.  We ordered the spicy ahi tuna bowl, spam sushi and beef tongue. Everything was incredible!!  So so fresh. The ahi bowl had so many toppings! Far from boring. The beef tongue, was a rare sight. Didn’t expect to find that in Hawaii, but it was just like I remember from Japan!  Would definitely come back to try the other dishes! Like a Japanese/ Hawaiian izakaya style food.
Rooftop restaurant with shockingly incredible food... easy 5 stars.  The ahi poke bowl is literally the best I’ve ever had.

Very inviting restaurant with outdoor seating. Good menu with choices for every palate! We had a yen for pizza and tried the Hawaiian Kailua Pork Pizza along with their Smoked Chicken Caesar Salad. Both were excellent! Will most definitely revisit this restaurant to try other items on the menu!
Very cool place with the open, 2nd floor, balconies to people watch! Pork nachos were excellent and LOADED (REALLY, amazing amount) with toppings! Fish and chips were great as well!
Beer was good, food was alright

Cute place but unfortunately had a bad experience. No communication between staff. Three different servers took our order and nothing came out on time. The main dish came out before the appetizer. We had the table's next to us food and heard them complaining about the wait. We decided to pay our bill and instead of cashing out us, two different servers argued with us and made excuses. The main server blamed the new hire for the mix up and he was actually the most professional out of the three. Icing on the cake, the waitress said, "Hopefully, you come back on a night that we're not busy". No thanks. Plenty of other fantastic restaurants in the area.

Our kids from Mountain View Californua brought the family in for Happy Hour and we all left HAPPY! We tried the calamari, to-die-for! The french fries, so ono! The Poke and the Blackened Ahi - OMG!!! We can't wait to walk down here again and Uber home.  Happy hour is from 6 to 8 😁

We will go back and try more off their menu before we leave.
